+## Supabase configuration
+
+All Supabase project values come from `.env`, so changing projects only means editing `.env` and relinking the CLI.
+
+1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env`.
+2. Set `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`, `VITE_SUPABASE_URL`, and `VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` for your project.
+3. Link the CLI to the same project, then push migrations:
+
+```sh
+supabase link --project-ref <your-project-ref>
+supabase db push
+```
+
+The app does not need `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` for local login or the first dealer bootstrap. After signing in, click **Make me the dealer**; the timestamped migration installs the required `claim_first_dealer_admin()` function.
+
